# ── Public-promotion repo hygiene · DEFAULT-DENY ────────────────────────────
# This repo is a PUBLIC calling card. Nothing is publishable unless explicitly
# allow-listed below. This makes an accidental `git add -A` unable to stage a
# private skill — and unlike .git/info/exclude, this file is COMMITTED, so the
# protection survives a fresh clone on any machine. Add a new public skill only
# by adding an explicit `!/<skill>/` line here.

# Ignore everything at the repo root by default …
/*

# … then allow repo metadata …
!/.gitignore
!/LICENSE
!/README.md

# … and ONLY the public skills.
!/analogy/
!/statusline/

# Keep this internal note out of the public analogy skill (was in info/exclude).
analogy/domains/README.md

# Re-ignore real secrets anywhere, even inside an allow-listed public skill.
# A whitelisted skill dir would otherwise expose any real env file dropped into
# it (e.g. statusline/.worldcup.env). The blank *.example files are NOT matched
# by these patterns, so they still publish.
**/.env
**/.worldcup.env
.worldcup.env

# Re-ignore junk anywhere, including inside the allowed public skills.
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.pyc
__pycache__/
